(39, 202, 'One Line Inc. Policies Statement', 'one-line-inc-policies-statement', '<p> <strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">1. How to become a Customer</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">You must: (A) have a sponsor who submits an Independent Marketing Executive Agreement; (B) you must sign and submit a Customer Membership Agreement; and (C) pay the cost of enrollment. A customer is not authorized sell or resell One Line products unless he or she has signed and submitted an Independent Marketing Executive Agreement to One Line as directed.</span></p>\r\n<p> <strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">2. How to becoming a Marketing Executive</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">You must (A) have a sponsor who has submitted an Independent Marketing Executive Agreement; (B) sign and submit your own Independent Marketing Executive Agreement; and (C) pay for your Independent Marketing Executive Agreement. After you have completed those steps, you are legally eligible to sell One Line products/services/memberships and to sign-up new One Line customers and Marketing Executives. Note: you do not become a Marketing Executive, until: (i) One Line receives your Independent Marketing Executive Agreement; (ii) you have a Customer or Marketing Executive in your own Marketing Organization; and (iii) you receive your first commission. You may purchase One Line products for yourself from One Line at the Direct Customer price. In the state of North Dakota, the purchase of a “membership kit” is optional.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">3. Individuals, Corporations, Tax Exempt Entities and Trusts</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line only accepts as Marketing Executives people or legal entities which meet one of the following categories:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(a) Individuals who meet the legal age.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(b) Married couples at least one is of whose is of the legal age.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(c) Corporations in good standing in the legal location of their incorporation and which have as their only officer, director(s) or shareholder(s) either married couple or one unmarried person.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(d) Entities which are both tax exempt and registered and</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Good standing as tax exempt institutions under Section 501(c)(3) of the United States Internal Revenue Code or under Section 248(1) of the Income Tax Act of Canada.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(e) Trusts established appropriate US or Canadian law and in good standing.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(f) Other charitable giving corporations or trusts or entities approved by One Line.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">4. Joint Ownership of a One Line Business</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Independent One Line Businesses may only be owned by an individual, a married couple, corporations, tax exempt entities or trusts that comply with One Line’s guidelines. A couple who jointly own an Independent One Line Business and who divorce may apply to have their Independent One Line Business reassigned to one of them as the sole owner. Said divorced couple must submit a written request to One Line a specifying to which person the Independent One Line Business will be transferred. The request must include the notarized signature of both parties OR it must include the notarized signature of at least one party AND include a certified copy of the court approved divorce decree or a property settlement that designates the party to which the Independent One Line Business should be transferred. One Line will consider any such request or court decree but retains the right to approve or disapprove of such a transfer request at its sole discretion. If One Line approves the transfer, the person to whom the Independent One Line Business is transferred must sign and submit to One Line a new Independent Marketing Executive Agreement.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">5. One Business per Person or Couple</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">A Marketing Executive may not operate, own or have a financial interest in more than one Independent One Line Business without One Line’s knowledge and express written approval. With regard to married couples and non-married cohabiting couples, both persons will be treated as a single Marketing Executive for purposes of One Line’s policies. Therefore, for example, if one person owns an Independent One Business, the other person may not own, operate or have a financial interest in a separate Independent One Line Business. Likewise, if a couple owns jointly an Independent One Line Business, neither party may own, operate nor have a financial interest in a separate Independent One Line Business. However, if two people who own separate Independent One Line Businesses marry or cohabit, they may each retain ownership of their separate businesses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">6. Marketing Executive and Customer Numbers</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives and Customers must only use with One Line the Social Security Number, portion of a Social Insurance Number, Social Insurance Number, Tax Revenue Number, TIN or Taxpayer Identification Number or Corporate Account Number or similar legally binding numbers those that have legally been assigned to the Marketing Executive or the Customer by the authorized governmental agency.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">7. Documents must be completed legally</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Any and all One Line contracts <span style="text-decoration: underline;">must</span> be filled out completely and properly and, if requested, signed. Alterations will not be accepted, nor will copies be accepted when originals are required. An altered agreement will not be legally acceptable by One Line. The payment of commissions or the passage of time does not forgive this violation and One Line shall not be responsible for the loss of bonuses or commissions or orders or for delays in Marketing Executive or Customer registrations due to: (A) Marketing Executives or Customer errors in preparation or transmittal of orders, agreements, or any other documents; (B) tardiness or inaccuracies caused by mail or fax transmissions; (C) One Line’s non-receipt of documents; (D) agreements, orders or other documents which are illegible or incomplete; or (E) Marketing Executives or Customers inability to contact One Line by phone or fax during calling periods that are busy. One Line processes and credits enrollments and orders in the calendar month in which they are received.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">8. Inheritance of Business</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">An Independent One Line Business may be inherited by a single person, a married couple or a trust which complies with One Line’s guidelines, pursuant to</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">a valid will or other appropriate legal document, or in accordance with the intestacy laws of the state, province, or country in which the Marketing Executive resides. The person(s) or entity who/which inherits an Independent One Line Business must expeditiously provide One Line with valid documentation that s/he or it is the legal beneficiary and is legally authorized to represent the estate. S/he or it must execute a Customer Agreement and an Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, and fulfill all of a Marketing Executive’s functions and comply with the terms of One Line’s Policy Statement.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">9. The Transfer or Sale of a One Line Business</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Before a Marketing Executive can transfer or sell his or her Independent One Line Business (except for Inheritance of Business) the following requirements must all be met:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A)  The transfer must be approved by One Line in writing.  It must be as in the best interest of all parties: (i) including the transferor,(ii) the transferee, (iii) One Line, and (iv) the members of the Marketing Organization of the transferor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B)  One Line must receive and accept fully completed and signed (with original signatures) and notarized Organization Sale Request and Organization Purchase Request forms.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C)  The transferee must complete and submit to One Line an Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, if there is not one on file.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(D)  The transfer will not constitute the purchase of position or marketing status by the transferee. The Marketing Executive’s One Line status must equal the potential status which the Marketing Executive could attain based on his or her own position at both the time of the transfer and for a fair period of time prior to the transfer, and the transferor Marketing Executive must have been the actual enroller of all personal enrollees and must have been involved in actively working with his or her personal directors. Marketing Executives may not contract/agree or allow another person to work their Independent One Line Business to bring</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(E)  Their business up to its specific status or offer to sell their business to another person on the condition that said person bring the business up to a specific status.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(F)  Both the transferor Marketing Executive and the Independent One Line Business must be at the time and for the entire twelve month period preceding the transfer including the month in which the transfer occurs be in compliance with all of One Line’s policies and of the terms of the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(G)  The transferee of the business agrees to undergo if he or she has not undergone, such orientation and training as One Line may require relative to the size of the business to be purchased.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">10. Ordering</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Customers are urged to order early each month. Orders received by One Line in a particular calendar month are credited to that month. To determine the month a product order occurs, a calendar month ends on the last day of a calendar month at midnight Pacific Time and begins on the first day of the next month at 12:01 AM Pacific Time. Orders can be placed via phone, mail, fax or the Internet. Phone or fax orders must be paid by Discover, Visa, MasterCard, or electronic checking. Mail orders may be paid by check, money order, Discover, Visa, MasterCard or electronic checking. Credit card payments must include the card number and expiration date. Marketing Executives and Customers are subject to being charged $10US/$15CDN for insufficient funds checks returned to One Line.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line will usually process all orders within 48 hours of receipt of the order. While delivery should be expected within 3 to 10 days, the carrier utilized by One Line will be of One Line’s choice. Orders placed during particularly busy times of the month may be delayed.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">11. Guarantee of Customer Satisfaction</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If any Customer who purchases a produce is not completely satisfied for any reason with a One Line product, the Customer may contact One Line with a copy of the purchase receipt within 90 days of the purchase date and One Line will provide the Customer with three options: (1) The Customer’s account will be credited for the full purchase price of the product), or (2) The product will be replaced at no charge to the Customer, or (3) The Customer will be given full credit toward another product from One Line. As a normal practice, cash refunds, will not be given; although One Line reserves all rights at its sole discretion. Further, One Line reserves the unilateral right to cancel the Customer Agreement of any and all Customers who abuses One Line’s Guarantee of Customer Satisfaction by excessive product returns.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">12. Return Adjustments</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fast Start packages</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Refunds for Fast Start commissions will be deducted from the Marketing Executive’s check in the month.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line reserves to itself the right to unilaterally terminate any Independent Marketing Executive Agreement or the Customer Membership Agreement of either a Marketing Executive or Customer who abuses One Line’s Guarantee of Customer Satisfaction by excessive returns.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">13. Marketing Executive Refund</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">A Marketing Executive applicant who enrolls and purchases a Marketing Executive Membership will be credited at One Line with a Membership in the name of the applicant. Any Marketing Executive applicant who cancels his or her Independent Marketing Executive Agreement and who returns to One Line their paid for Membership Kit within 120 days of the date of enrollment, One Line will give the Marketing Executive a full refund for the cost of the Membership. The Marketing Executive’s refund will be returned to the name the on the Executive’s Membership. It doesn’t matter if the Marketing Executive applicant purchases his Membership directly from One Line or from his or her Sponsor. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">14. Rights of Customers and Marketing Executives to Cancel Agreements</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">A Customer may cancel his or her Customer Membership at any time for any reason by sending One Line a Cancellation Form available from One Line or by giving written notice to One Line which is signed by him or her with an original signature with the Customer’s One Line name printed together with their address, Customer Identification Number an explanation for canceling so that One Line can improve its Customer service. Utilizing One Line’s cancellation form will insure that One Line receives accurate information to facilitate the cancellation. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If an individual or entity is a Customer and a Marketing Executive, the notice should indicate which agreement(s) the individual wants canceled. All written cancellations received by One Line on or by the 24th of the month will be immediately effective for the month in which it is received. All written cancellations received by One Line after the 25<sup>th</sup> of the month will be effective the first of the following month. Letters of cancellation must be mailed to: One Line; 808 E Valley Blvd.; San Gabriel, CA.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">15. Cancellation Refund Policy for Marketing Executives</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line will repurchase from Marketing Executives who cancel their Independent Marketing Executive Agreements all unsold products which are in condition to resell which were bought by the Marketing Executive from One Line over the prior 12 months The price that One Line will pay will be not less than ninety percent (90%) of the original net cost paid by the Marketing Executive. All products must be returned by the Marketing Executive to One Line with shipping prepaid by the Marketing Executive to receive this refund. One Line will charge back any and all bonuses, commissions and rebates paid by One Line connected with the purchases of the above referenced products.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">16. Questions or Errors</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives should immediately notify One Line of any errors or questions about commissions, bonuses, Monthly Business Reports, orders or charges. One Line will correct any errors reported to it within 60 days, but  omissions or problems not reported within 60 days are not the responsibility of One Line.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">17. Cancellation Refund Policy for Marketing Executives in Georgia</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line will repurchase from Marketing Executives who cancel their Independent Marketing Executive Agreements pursuant to Rights of Customers and Marketing Executives to Cancel Agreements Policy all products, sales materials including literature which are in reasonably resalable or reusable condition and which were purchased by the Marketing Executive from One Line, at not less than ninety percent (90%) of the Marketing Executive’s original net cost. Goods shall be deemed in “resalable or reusable” condition if the goods are either in an unused or commercially resalable condition at the time the goods are received by One Line. One Line will also repay ninety percent (90%) of the Marketing Executive’s fees paid for services which have not been received by the Marketing Executive when the agreement is cancelled. The Marketing Executive must prepay all shipping in order to receive this refund. One Line will charge back any and all bonuses, commissions and rebates paid by One Line connected with the purchases of the above referenced products or services.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">18. Organizational Transfer Within One Line</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Customers and Marketing Executives may transfer from (one) One Line organization to another One Line organization.  However, all of the following conditions must be completed:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(i) The Marketing Executive or Customer seeking to change organization must submit a One Line Organization Change form including original signatures of the Marketing Executives in all seven generations above either the Marketing Executive or the Customer;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(ii) If the Marketing Executive seeking the organization change has no more than 10 Customers in his or her existing Marketing Organization and will have no more than 10 Customers in the Marketing Organization into which he or she is  moving;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iii) The Marketing Executive or Customer seeking the organization change has paid to One Line any applicable fee charged by One Line for organization changes;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iv) One Line must approved any change in writing and One Line may withhold said approval for any reason.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">19. Conduct of Members of the Household</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Any member of the Marketing Executive’s Immediate Household who engages in any activity that would violate any One Line policy or any provision of the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, such activity will be deemed a violation by the Marketing Executive.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">20. Non-Solicitation and Conflicts of Interest</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives as independent contractors may be active in other business ventures while they are Marketing Executives for One Line. Marketing Executives have the responsibility to motive, train, service, supervise, and assist their Marketing Organizations’ Marketing Executives to qualify for compensation under One Line’s Compensation Plan. They are responsible for promoting One Line’s products and the One Line income opportunity. One Line together with its Marketing Executives have made a major investment in creating businesses consisting of Marketing Executives and their Customers. This network is One Line’s most valuable asset. One Line reserves the option or right to decline to pay any compensation to any Marketing Executive who recruits any One Line Customer or Marketing Executive to participate in another business. To protect all Marketing Executives in building and maintaining their Marketing Organizations and Customer networks, and to protect One Line’s overall Customer base, all Marketing Executives and all members of their immediate family and/or household are required to strictly follow these policies:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) Non-Solicitation of One Line Customers and Marketing Executives:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(i) During the time that Independent Marketing Executive Agreements are binding Marketing Executives and all members of their immediate family and/or Household are prohibited both directly and indirectly or through any third party from recruiting One Line Customers or Marketing Executives to join any other business.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(ii) Marketing Executives for a period of twelve months after cancellation or termination of a Marketing Executive’s Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, said Marketing Executive and all members of his or her immediate family or household are prohibited from directly, indirectly or through a third party recruiting to join in any other business any One Line Customers or Marketing Executives:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 90px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(1) people who were part of the Marketing Executive’s</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 90px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Organization or Support Team at any time while he or she were association with One Line;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 90px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(2) people who the Marketing Executive had contact with during his or her association with One Line;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 90px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(3) people whose contact information including just the name the Marketing Executive or members of his or her immediate family or household obtained during his or her association with One Line; or</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 90px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(4) people any part of whose contact information the Marketing Executive or members of his or her immediate family or household obtained at any time from someone who obtained the contact information because of any association with One Line.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The prohibitions in clauses (A) (1) and (2) above are not limited to, presentations (or assisting in the presentations) of other business opportunities to even a single One Line Customer or Marketing Executive.  Also prohibited is either implicitly or explicitly encouraging in any way any One Line Customer or Marketing Executive to join another other business. A lack of knowledge of a person’s involvement with One Line does not prevent a violation of this policy.  The Marketing Executive is responsibility or determining whether a person is a One Line Marketing Executive or Customer before enticing a person to join another business. (The Definitions of Terms at the end of these Policies cover the definition of the word recruit for the purposes of this section.  Please familiarize yourself with the definitions.)</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) During the period that an individual’s Independent Marketing Executive Agreements are binding and for the twelve months period after the cancellation or termination thereof for whatever reason, Marketing Executives and all members of their immediate family or household are also prohibited from:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(i) Any role in the production of tapes or promotional</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">material of any kind, websites, or emails, or list maintenance for this purpose utilized by the Marketing Executive or any other person or persons to solicit One Line Customers or Marketing Executives to participate in another business;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(ii) Promoting or selling any competing products or services to One Line Customers;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iii) Offering non-One Line products or business opportunities in conjunction with the offering One Line products or business opportunities at any One Line meeting or event, or function.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C) (i) Violation of any provision of the Non-Solicitation and Conflicts of Interest Policy will be considered a Marketing Executive’s voluntary resignation and his or her cancelation of their Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, as of the date of the violation.  The Marketing Executive will forfeit all commissions or bonuses not yet paid including the month in which the Policy violation occurred.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(ii) If the Marketing Executive receives any bonuses or commission after the date of the violation, all compensation for the calendar month in which the violation occurred or subsequent months shall be refunded to One Line.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iii) One Line may seek and secure both injunctive relief and damages from the Marketing Executive for violations of this Policy. One Line legally retains the right to lawsuit in a court of competent jurisdiction to enforce its rights. </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iv) In addition to refunds of bonuses and commissions and to damages as described above, in the event a person or entity violates this Policy 20, One Line, and any Marketing Executive who is adversely impacted as a result of said violation of this Policy are entitled to both an accounting and repayment of all remunerations and any and all other benefits which the violator or violating entity receives and/or may receive directly or indirectly as a result of, growing out of, or in connection with any violation of this Policy.  This remedy shall be in addition to and not in limitation of any damages, or injunctive relief or other rights or remedies to which One Line is or may be entitled at law or in equity.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(d) Since violations of this Policy are especially damaging to both One Line and to the growth and sales of other Marketing Executives’ Independent One Line Businesses; Marketing Executives who have knowledge of any violation of this Policy must report said violation immediately to One Line’s Legal Counsel. If a Marketing Executive fails to report such a violation, said failure will also constitute a violation of this Policy. (People who report violations of this Policy will be held in the strictest of confidence.)</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">21. Trade Secrets and Proprietary Information</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">By signing the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, a Marketing Executive understands and agrees that all information contained in a Marketing Executive’s Monthly Business Report, including names and contact information of Marketing Executives and Customers, and any and all identifying information relating to other Marketing Executives or customers that the Marketing Executive acquires while conducting any One Line business or while attending One Line events related to One Line, is One Line’s proprietary trade secret information. All Marketing Executives agree to not disclose any such information to anyone other than existing or prospective One Line Marketing Executives or Customers for the purpose of promoting One Line products and business opportunities.  Marketing Executives agree not to utilize such information for to promote any other business at any time, either while with One Line or after. Every Marketing Executive understands that proprietary information is of such nature and importance that disclosure or use thereof is violation of this Policy and will result in irreparable damage to both One Line and to Independent One Line Businesses. One Line and its Marketing Executives will be entitled to injunctive relief from a court to prevent violation of this policy. If litigation or arbitration is necessary to obtain court relief or to recover damages, the prevailing party shall be entitled to attorney’s fees and all expenses.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">22. The Prohibition On Excess Inventory Purchases</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line’s marketing is based on End Customer sales. End Consumers must purchase at least 70% of a Marketing Executive Organization’s monthly purchases each month.  If a Marketing Executive arranges himself or herself or through another party to purchase product solely to qualifying for compensation, such purchases will constitutes fraud by the Marketing Executive.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">23. Selling in Stores Prohibited</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line is a personal businesses based on personal presentations of One Line’s products. To maintain this business model, Marketing Executives may not sell or even display One Line products in any physical business selling to the general public. It is incumbent upon the Marketing Executive to control the appropriate and effective presentation or display of One Line products to potential Customers.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">24. The Enroller</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) Only the Marketing Executive who is the Enroller of a new Customer or Marketing Executive may list such new Customer or Marketing Executive. It doesn’t matter where a Customer or Marketing Executive is placed in a Marketing Organization, the Marketing Executive who is the Enroller of such Customer or Marketing Executive must be listed as the Enroller on the Customer Membership Agreement.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) The Enroller and any other Marketing Executives involved in the recruitment and enrollment of a new Marketing Executive may use only One Line’s products and One Line’s compensation plan and their promise to help the new Marketing Executive build his or her new business to encourage a new Marketing Executive to enroll. Marketing Executives are prohibited from using special arrangements or promises with an Enrollee, relating to, but not limited to, promises payment of money or special promotions.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">25. Leadership and Supervisory Functions</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Every Marketing Executives’ compensation is based on product purchased by the Consumers. To qualify, Marketing Executives are responsible for promoting the One Line business opportunity, upholding One Line’s policies and practices, and to motivate, train, supervise and service their Marketing Executives to promote and sell and One Line products and the related One Line business opportunity. If a Marketing Executive attempts to convince or encourage a Customer or Marketing Executive to cease or reduce purchasing One Line’s products, or to transfer from one One Line Marketing Organization to a separate Marketing Organization, to cease or reduce the promotion of the One Line business opportunity, or to consider another direct selling business (directly competitive or not), or to criticize One Line, One Line products, or One Line’s management team, personnel, or marketing practices will be violations of the Marketing Executive’s responsibility as a leader and will be a violation of this policy.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">26. Compensation and Monthly Business Reports</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">All compensation shall usually be paid by One Line to Marketing Executives on or around the 15th day of each month for compensation earned in the prior month. If that date falls on either a weekend or US holiday, checks will usually be paid on the next US business day. Every Marketing Executive who qualifies for compensation will receive a Monthly Business Report reporting on activity with each Customer and Marketing Executive in his or her Marketing Organization.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Monthly Business Reports will show how the Marketing Executive’s compensation was calculated. Monthly Business Reports will provide Marketing Executives with a road map to manage and supervise as well as ID potential training or support needs of the members of their Marketing Organizations.  Both the information and the systems contained in One Line’s Business Reports are proprietary trade secret information, and it is a violation of policy for Marketing Executives to share said information.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">See Policy</span> on <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Trade Secrets and Proprietary Information for further information on all Marketing Executives’ obligations with regard to proprietary trade secret information such as the above. Marketing Executives will be charged a data processing fee for producing their personalized Monthly Business Reports.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Compensation checks which go uncashed for more than 180 days will not be honored by One Line and the check amount, less a handling fee of $15.00US/$22.50CDN plus a bank stop payment fee of $10.00US/$15.00CDN, will be credited by One Line to the Marketing Executive’s account. Said credit can be used by the Marketing Executive for future purchases. A Marketing Executive whose account is not active will be notified of the account credit, and said account will be debited a service charge of $10.00US/$15.00CDN for each notice sent to the Marketing Executive.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">27. Limitations on Purchases for Other Persons</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line Marketing Executives may neither order nor pay for products for Customers unless said Customer expressly authorizes and agrees to pay the Marketing Executive for said product.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">28. Restrictions on International Marketing </span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives who are enrolled in either the United States or Canada may sell One Line products and enroll Customers and Marketing Executives in either the US or Canada. In all other countries where One Line or  affiliate companies are conduct business, Marketing Executives may enroll both Customers and Marketing Executives under One Line’s International Program. Marketing Executives and Customers may not sell or transship One Line products over any international border for sale or resale, except as specified for the U.S./ Canadian border and all products must be properly labeled for the destination country. Not only are Marketing Executives and Customers prohibited from the sale or export/import or distribution of One Line products or One Line business tools to any country (other than the US and Canada). If a Marketing Executive or Customer has reason to believe someone is exporting products to another country, they are prohibited from allowing or facilitating said purchases from One Line and are required to notify One Line’s Corporate Offices.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">29. Trademark, Service Mark and Trade Name Restrictions</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives and Customers are prohibited from reproducing or disseminating the One Line trade name, logo or any One Line trademark or service mark except in the use and dissemination of literature published and made available by One Line and except on stationery and business cards produced and/or authorized by One Line. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">30. Rules Governing Advertising, Internet Usage and Sale of Materials</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) Marketing Executives are prohibited from:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(i) creating, publishing, promoting/selling/distributing/using, any written or printed material, audio or video recording or similar or related electronic materials including social networking sites, web site, automated or similar phone message, Internet bulletin board or message, non-individualized or spam email message, or infomercial that represents One Line or its products or its business opportunity (with or without information on One Line’s compensation plan) in any way other than as permitted and set forth in this Policy and One’s Guidelines on Internet Usage or which is created and provided by One Line;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(ii) duplicate any materials produced by One Line except as outlined pursuant to this policy;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iii) utilize One Line’s name or logo or the name or logo of any of One Line’s products in <strong>any</strong> material (broadly construed) placed in but not limited to a publication, on radio or TV, or the web in Internet or email format or directories, or phone. A Marketing Executive may utilize various directory listing(s) as follows:  “One Line Independent Marketing Executive—name of Marketing Executive”;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(iv) A Marketing Executive must have prior written approval from One Line to showcase or advertise either One Line’s products or One Line’s business opportunity at fairs, trade shows, flea markets or comparable event, </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 60px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(v) may not charge people for the right to attend One Line related meetings or events created by a Marketing Executive or where a Marketing Executive is showcased.   It is permissible to charge if necessary to recoup the actual expenses incurred by the Marketing Executive</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) Marketing Executives are encouraged to use One Line websites and personal email messages in accordance with One Line’s Guidelines on Internet Usage. One Line retains sole discretion to update or modify said Guidelines. One Line will periodically publish updates to the Guidelines on its website. The Marketing Executives shall periodically review the Guidelines and comply with all updates.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C) One Line will provide Marketing Executives with the only approved websites which the Marketing Executives may utilize. </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(D) One Line will have the absolute right to remove any One Line related website or to require same of any Marketing Executive or Customer, together with any related forum, message board or email. If a Marketing Executive must comply within the time specified by One Line. Violations of this policy may result in forfeiture of compensation and/or in termination of the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement of the Marketing Executive.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">31. Income Claims</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It will be a violation of Policy for any Marketing Executive to make false or misleading representations about either their own or other Marketing Executives’ compensation from the One Line or false or misleading statements about One Line’s Compensation Plan. If a Marketing Executive makes any claim regarding his or her own compensation from One Line with the apparent intent to directly or indirectly recruit a new Marketing Executive, the Marketing Executive making the claim must show the person(s) hearing the claim One Line’s current Marketing Executives Annual Income Statistics sheet for themselves.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">32. Media Inquiries</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line’s policy is to have a corporate representative respond to all media inquiries and all media relations without exception. Consistent with this Policy, Marketing Executives are prohibited from discussing either their own Independent One Line Business, or act as representatives for One Line, or communicating in any way with the media about One Line, its business plan, or its products. Therefore, this policy will be considered to have been violated by anyone affiliated with One Line, or for 12 months after any Marketing Executive leaves One Line, to communicate with the media in any way, even if the intent is to provide positive information about One Line. All inquiries from the radio, television, print or online must be referred to One Line Corporate Offices.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">33. Product Claims and/or Warranties</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives may only utilize the One Line product claims and uses  published by One Line and are prohibit from making any additional product claims or product warranties. Marketing Executives shall not cite any other claims or uses, even if true.  Any One Line product claims, uses or warranties which are country specific may not be utilized by any Marketing Executive in any another country.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">34. Ethical Sales Standards and Practices</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives shall:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Conduct themselves not just professionally, but with courtesy, and in a kind or Christian manner;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Represent One Line and its products in a sincere and open way that complies with One Line’s Customer Satisfaction Guarantee;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Represent the One Line’s Compensation Plan only as outlined in One Line’s published Compensation Plan;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Study and utilize One Line’s sales approaches, Compensation Plan and Policies Statement, and such other materials provided by One Line;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Present One Line’s business opportunity consistent with One Line’s promotional material and training; </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Provide training as well as motivation and support to their organization’s</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives shall not:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Be involved or condone unlawful, unethical or deceptive business or recruiting practice(s);</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Be involved in or condone high pressure selling or recruiting;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Be involved in enrolling either minors or persons incapable of making an informed decision.  This applies to both Customer Membership Agreement and Independent Marketing Executive Agreement;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">• Be involved in violating or circumventing One Line’s policies</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">35. Policy Disclosure Requirement</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">When enrolling a Marketing Executive, Marketing Executives shall provide a copy of One Line’s Policies Statements and Definitions of Terms.  The enrolling Marketing Executive shall review said material and answer all questions before completing the enrollment.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">36. Voluntary Resignation Due to Inactivity</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Marketing Executives are responsible for leading his or her Marketing Organization through the example of selling and recruiting new Marketing Executives. If a Marketing Executive becomes inactive, he or she will cease to receive compensation from his or her Marketing Organization. Marketing Executives who sell less than the minimum volume of products required to maintain their current Compensation Rate during any given month, as provided in the Compensation Plan, will not be paid compensation based on such status from their Marketing Organization for that month. If a Marketing Executive sells less than the minimum volume of products for two consecutive months that will constitute a voluntary resignation by the Marketing Executive. A Marketing Executive who voluntarily resigns loses his or her Personal Enrollees and Marketing Organization. The effective date of the resignation is the day after the end of the second month of inactivity.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">37. Reactivation &amp; Reenrollment Requirements After A Voluntary Resignation For Inactivity</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) A Marketing Executive who voluntarily resigned under Policy</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Voluntary Resignation Due to Inactivity and who reactivates, he or she will reenter his or her previous Marketing Organization in the first position under his or her original Marketing Executive other than the position left vacant by his or her voluntary resignation.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">38. Positons Not Lost</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">A Marketing Executive can lose his or her unique Marketing Executive status and participatory rights in the corresponding compensation if he or she fails to continue to qualify for the compensation related to such status. As long as a Marketing Executive remains active, he or she will not lose the title of the highest status he or she has acquired.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">39. Roll-Up Policy</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) When a vacancy occurs in a Marketing Organization due to the inactivity, voluntary resignation or involuntary termination of a Marketing Executive each Marketing Executive in the level below the Canceled Marketing Executive will have the opportunity to roll up into the position of the Canceled Marketing Executive. The Marketing Executive over the Marketing Executive who voluntarily resigned shall select the replacement.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) The Enroller of a voluntarily or involuntarily terminated Marketing Executive will inherit the Canceled Marketing Executive’s Personal Enrollees.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C) No Enroller can inherit a Personal Enrollee whose Status is higher than his or her own.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">40. Marketing Executives are Independent Contractors and, as such, have certain Legal Obligations. Among those, Marketing Executives must:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) Comply with all federal, state, and local laws and ordinances relating to the purchase, delivery, storing, selling, distributing or promotion of One Line products and the One Line business opportunity;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) The Marketing Executive shall bare his or her own expense to create, sign, and file all legally required reports; and obtain to obtain any licenses that are required by law or government relating to his or her Independent One Line Business and/or One Line products;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C) Be personally liable for complying with and paying any and of all local, state, federal and general taxes or fees that result from the Marketing Executive’s Independent One Line Business;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(D) Provide all of his or her own equipment and supplies for his or her One Line Business, such as phone, transportation, office and office equipment and supplies; and</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(E) Provide his or her own business location and set his or her own work hours.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">41. Marketing Executives Do Not Represent the One Line Corporation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">As Independent Contractors, Marketing Executives do not represent the One Line Corporation and are not authorized to incur any expense or financial obligation on behalf of One Line Corporation nor legally bind One Line to any obligation or contract.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">42. One Line’s Corrective Actions</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">All policies in this Policies Statement, the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, and any and all other contracts entered into by and between One Line and One Line Marketing Executives are material terms to the agreement between One Line and One Line Marketing Executives. A Marketing Executive who violates any of the terms and conditions of any of these agreements or the Policies Statement or who commits any illegal, fraudulent, misleading or unethical conduct may result, at One Line’s sole discretion, in any or all of the following corrective measures:</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(A) One Line may issue a written warning or admonishment with or without conditions; </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(B) One Line may impose a fine which requires immediate payment or withheld said fine from future compensation;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(C) One Line may reassign any or all of the offending Marketing Executive’s Marketing Organization;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(D) One Line may suspend for one or more months the offending Marketing Executive’s Independent Marketing Executive Agreement; </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(E) One Line may cancel his or her Independent Marketing</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Executive Agreement; or</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">(F) One Line may impose any specific remedy outlined in any of the policies in the Policies Statement or referenced in the Marketing Executive Agreement, the Corporate Entity Application and Agreement</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line retains the exclusive right to withhold compensation from a Marketing Executive during any period that One Line is investigating any allegation(s) of the above behavior by a Marketing Executive. One Line retains the right to cancel a Marketing Executive’s Independent Marketing Executive Agreement prior to the investigation of a violation, and to withhold any and all compensation during the investigation.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">43. Forfeiture of Rights to Bonuses and Commissions</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">While a Marketing Executive is complying with all policies and terms of the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, One Line is obligated to pay all compensation to such Marketing Executive in accordance with the Compensation Plan. A Marketing Executive’s compensation constitute the entire financial consideration for all of the Marketing Executive’s efforts, and the Marketing Executive’s entire Marketing Organization. A Marketing Executive’s resignation, cancellation for inactivity, or voluntary or involuntary cancellation of his or her Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, results in such former Marketing Executive having no residual right, claim, title, or interest in the Marketing Organization. Said former Marketing Executive shall have no claim for compensation for the Marketing Organization or for sales produce by the Marketing Organization. Following cancellation (voluntary or involuntary) of his or her Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, former Marketing Executives shall not represent himself or herself as a One Line Marketing Executive or as having any right to sell One Line products.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">44. Policies Statement, Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, and Compensation Plan Amendments</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">One Line retains the right at its sole discretion to amend the Compensation Plan, Policies Statements, or any Definitions of Terms or the terms of the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement and any and all agreements entered into by and between One Line and the Marketing Executives by notifying Marketing Executives of the change(s). By signing the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement, Marketing Executives acknowledge and agree to abide by any such amendments. The acceptance of compensation by a Marketing Executive from One Line or the continuation of his or her Independent One Line Business constitutes his or her acceptance of any such amendments. The most current versions of the Compensation Plan, the Statement of Policies, any Definitions of Terms, the Independent Marketing Executive Agreement and any other agreements entered into by and between One Line and the Marketing Executives shall be controlling.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">.<img src="images/policy1.jpg" alt="" width="540" height="703" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/policy2.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/policy3.jpg" alt="" width="543" height="367" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">       </p>', '', 1, 2, '2015-04-06 23:04:36', 994, '', '2015-04-07 17:41:15', 994, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-04-06 23:04:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 7, 1, '', '', 1, 2531, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '');
